1
00:00:01,482 --> 00:00:07,187
♪♪

2
00:00:07,322 --> 00:00:08,572
Look at that, Tank!

3
00:00:09,894 --> 00:00:11,364
Cloudsdale's here!

4
00:00:11,688 --> 00:00:14,193
That means Ponyville
is next up for winter!

5
00:00:16,989 --> 00:00:23,494
[rumbling]

6
00:00:23,545 --> 00:00:26,471
You're doing awesome,
everypony! Keep it up!

7
00:00:26,623 --> 00:00:29,023
We need those leaves
off those trees!

8
00:00:31,557 --> 00:00:35,604
Once we get autumn cleared
away, it'll be "Hello, Winter!"

9
00:00:35,974 --> 00:00:38,753
[yawn]

10
00:00:39,566 --> 00:00:42,290
Was that a yawn
I just saw?

11
00:00:44,261 --> 00:00:47,136
How can you be tired when the
most exciting time of the year

12
00:00:47,153 --> 00:00:48,618
is right around the corner!

13
00:00:48,947 --> 00:00:51,237
And don't forget
the best part...

14
00:00:51,494 --> 00:00:53,726
our first winter together!

15
00:00:57,553 --> 00:00:59,507
Come on, wake up!

16
00:00:59,646 --> 00:01:01,734
Once those ponies bring in
the big fat clouds

17
00:01:01,751 --> 00:01:04,277
full of snowflakes, we'll
have a ton of snow

18
00:01:04,290 --> 00:01:06,244
for our extreme sledding!

19
00:01:09,355 --> 00:01:10,176
Ha ha ha!

20
00:01:10,250 --> 00:01:11,738
Whoa!

21
00:01:11,764 --> 00:01:12,846
Whoo hoo!

22
00:01:15,414 --> 00:01:17,351
And over there we can
play horse hockey!

23
00:01:17,738 --> 00:01:19,242
With no shoulder or rump pads!

24
00:01:22,576 --> 00:01:25,178
[cheering crowd]

25
00:01:28,938 --> 00:01:30,947
Everything's looking
great, don't you think?

26
00:01:31,162 --> 00:01:34,640
Almost everything. Does
Tank look all right to you?

27
00:01:34,968 --> 00:01:36,324
[yawn]

28
00:01:37,073 --> 00:01:39,848
Well, he does seem to be
moving a little slowly.

29
00:01:40,176 --> 00:01:41,343
I know, right?

30
00:01:42,185 --> 00:01:44,000
And he looks kind
of sleepy...

31
00:01:44,955 --> 00:01:45,941
Totally!

32
00:01:46,126 --> 00:01:47,633
just like he always does.

33
00:01:47,962 --> 00:01:50,614
Yeah, heh-heh, I'm
sure you're right.

34
00:01:52,395 --> 00:01:54,673
[yawn]

35
00:02:02,556 --> 00:02:07,550
HoH Subtitles by YayPonies
We have Muffins
http://main.yayponies.eu

36
00:02:36,450 --> 00:02:40,172
[very slow heart beat]

37
00:02:40,496 --> 00:02:41,477
Well?

38
00:02:41,865 --> 00:02:45,827
I suppose his heartbeat
COULD be a teensy, weensy,

39
00:02:45,983 --> 00:02:48,362
eensy bit slower than usual.

40
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:51,149
OK, so give him a
vitamin or something.

41
00:02:51,204 --> 00:02:55,271
[snoring]

42
00:02:55,637 --> 00:02:57,141
I don't think he
needs that.

43
00:02:57,448 --> 00:02:58,976
Maybe we're just
staying up too late.

44
00:02:59,393 --> 00:03:00,993
Too many Derring-Do stories.

45
00:03:02,206 --> 00:03:03,591
That's not it either.

46
00:03:03,957 --> 00:03:06,307
Well, what's wrong
with him then?

47
00:03:06,576 --> 00:03:09,052
Nothing. He's
perfectly fine!

48
00:03:10,029 --> 00:03:11,120
[relieved sigh]

49
00:03:11,271 --> 00:03:12,778
He's just going
to hibernate.

50
00:03:13,869 --> 00:03:16,248
You do realize he's
not a bear, right?

51
00:03:16,425 --> 00:03:17,094
[giggle]

52
00:03:17,612 --> 00:03:20,311
When the weather grows cold
and less food is available,

53
00:03:20,395 --> 00:03:23,233
many animals hibernate
to conserve energy.

54
00:03:25,924 --> 00:03:28,821
It's like taking a really
long nap during winter.

55
00:03:29,684 --> 00:03:31,343
And then they wake
up in spring!

56
00:03:31,915 --> 00:03:34,189
And see? Even
tortoises do it.

57
00:03:34,404 --> 00:03:38,349
When the time comes, Tank will
leave and dig into the ground.

58
00:03:39,183 --> 00:03:40,534
[yawn]

59
00:03:40,993 --> 00:03:44,395
But don't worry, he'll
reappear when the spring sun

60
00:03:44,416 --> 00:03:46,336
warms the ground back up.

61
00:03:46,538 --> 00:03:49,296
Come on! Tortoises
don't hibernate.

62
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:51,709
Somepony put that picture
in there as a joke.

63
00:03:52,332 --> 00:03:53,953
It's not a joke.

64
00:03:54,122 --> 00:03:55,915
Well then your
book must be wrong.

65
00:03:57,642 --> 00:04:01,035
Rainbow Dash, Tank
needs to hibernate.

66
00:04:01,355 --> 00:04:04,690
It's healthy for him, just like
sleeping is healthy for us.

67
00:04:05,557 --> 00:04:08,766
Whatever, OK, thanks.
Come on, Tank.

68
00:04:12,825 --> 00:04:14,054
Where are you going?

69
00:04:14,265 --> 00:04:18,484
To get a second opinion from
a REAL reptile expert.

70
00:04:20,627 --> 00:04:23,612
I told you, Rainbow
Dash. I'm a DRAGON!

71
00:04:24,513 --> 00:04:27,296
Come on, you're
practically twins!

72
00:04:29,469 --> 00:04:30,589
I'm purple!

73
00:04:31,250 --> 00:04:34,004
But if you don't have to
hibernate, why should Tank?

74
00:04:34,328 --> 00:04:37,288
Because he's a TORTOISE.
And I'm a DRAGON.

75
00:04:37,949 --> 00:04:39,229
Same family though, right?

76
00:04:39,389 --> 00:04:40,480
No!

77
00:04:40,732 --> 00:04:42,122
I'll take that as a yes.

78
00:04:43,094 --> 00:04:45,823
Look, if Fluttershy says
tortoises hibernate,

79
00:04:45,856 --> 00:04:47,646
then I guarantee
tortoises hiber--

80
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:50,016
Well, what would you know?
You're a dragon!

81
00:04:50,762 --> 00:04:51,696
[slam]

82
00:04:53,574 --> 00:04:55,654
Nopony knows you like
I do, Tank.

83
00:04:55,840 --> 00:04:58,682
All you need is some hard work
to get the ol' blood pumping.

84
00:04:58,707 --> 00:05:02,724
[snoring]

85
00:05:03,120 --> 00:05:04,206
Come on!

86
00:05:05,770 --> 00:05:12,101
♪♪

87
00:05:12,858 --> 00:05:15,743
These things are heavy!
Chock full o' snowflakes.

88
00:05:16,004 --> 00:05:18,463
We're gonna have such a
killer time in the snow, Tank!

89
00:05:20,033 --> 00:05:24,522
Tank? TANK?

90
00:05:25,052 --> 00:05:28,261
Aw, look at that
cute wittle Tanky!

91
00:05:28,336 --> 00:05:32,324
All snuggly wuggly,
getting ready to hibern---

92
00:05:32,526 --> 00:05:34,332
DON'T SAY THAT WORD!

93
00:05:34,631 --> 00:05:37,709
Which one? Snuggly?
Wuggly? Tanky? Hiberna--

94
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:38,370
THAT ONE!

95
00:05:39,570 --> 00:05:40,858
I was just saying
how cute he loo--

96
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:44,829
If you think hiber-- you know,
that napping thing--

97
00:05:44,985 --> 00:05:47,886
is SOOO cute, why
don't you go do it?

98
00:05:48,218 --> 00:05:49,835
Somewhere far away from here!

99
00:05:54,774 --> 00:05:56,160
What are you looking at?

100
00:05:56,303 --> 00:05:59,237
Pinkie Pie and I are just
having a conversation!

101
00:06:00,341 --> 00:06:02,635
Look Rainbow Dash, we all
know how upset you are

102
00:06:02,652 --> 00:06:03,343
about Tank hiber--

103
00:06:03,368 --> 00:06:05,760
SHHHH! Don't say that word!

104
00:06:05,882 --> 00:06:07,145
That's what started this all!

105
00:06:07,498 --> 00:06:09,498
We know how upset
you are about Tank,

106
00:06:09,928 --> 00:06:12,071
but you shouldn't take your
anger out on your friends.

107
00:06:12,218 --> 00:06:14,008
WHO SAID ANYTHING ABOUT ANGER?

108
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:15,768
I DIDN'T SAY
ANYTHING ABOUT ANGER!

109
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:16,896
I'M NOT UPSET!

110
00:06:17,048 --> 00:06:18,665
AND I AM NOT ANGRY!

111
00:06:18,943 --> 00:06:20,067
DO I LOOK ANGRY?

112
00:06:22,711 --> 00:06:25,073
C'MON TANK, LET'S
GET OUTTA HERE!

113
00:06:29,793 --> 00:06:31,591
I need you bright-eyed
and bushy-tailed,

114
00:06:31,882 --> 00:06:33,987
not sleepy-eyed
and scaly-tailed...

115
00:06:34,597 --> 00:06:36,644
...which is
exactly what you are.

116
00:06:37,052 --> 00:06:38,416
But get up anyway!

117
00:06:39,785 --> 00:06:43,082
[yawn]

118
00:06:43,309 --> 00:06:45,898
You CAN'T hiber--you know!

119
00:06:46,277 --> 00:06:47,818
What about all the primo things

120
00:06:47,835 --> 00:06:49,397
we're gonna do
together this winter?

121
00:06:49,667 --> 00:06:52,496
Building snowponies,
starting snowball fights,

122
00:06:52,623 --> 00:06:55,010
sipping hot cider by the fire.

123
00:06:55,178 --> 00:06:57,890
[snoring]

124
00:06:58,143 --> 00:07:00,210
DON'T YOU WANT TO DO
THOSE THINGS WITH ME?

125
00:07:05,200 --> 00:07:06,888
Think, Rainbow Dash, think!

126
00:07:07,242 --> 00:07:09,995
Tank's only hibernating
because it's cold, right?

127
00:07:11,440 --> 00:07:14,749
Well, I'd rather have
him awake in the heat

128
00:07:15,010 --> 00:07:16,850
than asleep in the cold.

129
00:07:20,004 --> 00:07:23,002
I'll just have to STOP WINTER!

130
00:07:30,265 --> 00:07:31,907
So, where do
these clouds go?

131
00:07:32,143 --> 00:07:33,532
Over by Clear Skies.

132
00:07:33,692 --> 00:07:35,132
But there's Clear
Skies everywhere.

133
00:07:35,280 --> 00:07:37,035
Yo! Clear Skies
right here!

134
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:39,094
But there's Clear
Skies over there, too.

135
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,724
That's Open Skies.

136
00:07:40,909 --> 00:07:43,292
There's open
skies everywhere!

137
00:07:43,397 --> 00:07:45,448
I'm not everywhere;
I'm right here.

138
00:07:46,261 --> 00:07:48,926
Wait, so, you're Open Skies,
and you're Clear Skies...

139
00:07:49,031 --> 00:07:50,096
then what's all that?

140
00:07:50,248 --> 00:07:51,949
Open, Clear Skies!

141
00:07:52,808 --> 00:07:55,271
Hey! Where'd our
fluffy clouds go?

142
00:07:55,456 --> 00:07:57,364
Fluffy Clouds?
He's over there!

143
00:07:59,423 --> 00:08:02,833
Ha! Stopping winter is
gonna be a breeze!

144
00:08:07,629 --> 00:08:08,652
[pop]

145
00:08:09,755 --> 00:08:16,682
♪♪

146
00:08:16,837 --> 00:08:19,141
<i> ♪ When life gives you lemons ♪</i>

147
00:08:20,197 --> 00:08:22,640
<i> ♪ You can make lemonade ♪</i>

148
00:08:23,738 --> 00:08:25,936
<i>♪ But life gave me Tank, here ♪</i>

149
00:08:26,185 --> 00:08:29,204
<i> ♪ And my choice has</i>
<i> long been made. ♪</i>

150
00:08:30,505 --> 00:08:33,680
<i> ♪ No winter will come to</i>
<i> Ponyville ♪</i>

151
00:08:33,877 --> 00:08:36,774
<i> ♪ I'll do it on my own ♪</i>

152
00:08:37,301 --> 00:08:39,886
<i> ♪ I will keep you by my side ♪</i>

153
00:08:39,903 --> 00:08:44,168
<i> ♪ So I will not be alone! ♪</i>

154
00:08:44,185 --> 00:08:45,002
♪♪

155
00:08:45,132 --> 00:08:51,385
<i> ♪ And I'll fly, and I'll fly</i>
<i> until the end of the sky ♪</i>

156
00:08:51,970 --> 00:08:58,016
<i> ♪ So I'll be the one who</i>
<i> doesn't have to say goodbye! ♪</i>

157
00:08:58,054 --> 00:08:59,473
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

158
00:08:59,705 --> 00:09:05,486
<i> ♪ I'll clear the skies forever</i>
<i> So we won't be apart ♪</i>

159
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:09,120
<i> ♪ I'll keep the</i>
<i> weather warm for you ♪</i>

160
00:09:09,347 --> 00:09:11,789
<i> ♪ And the winter will</i>
<i> never start! ♪</i>

161
00:09:11,835 --> 00:09:18,336
♪♪

162
00:09:18,501 --> 00:09:20,917
<i> ♪ Weather makers, Pegasi ♪</i>

163
00:09:21,865 --> 00:09:24,311
<i> ♪ You make the seasons</i>
<i> in the sky ♪</i>

164
00:09:25,448 --> 00:09:27,949
<i> ♪ I don't wanna sabotage you ♪</i>

165
00:09:27,991 --> 00:09:30,669
<i>♪ But you see I've got to try! ♪</i>

166
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:35,216
<i>♪ No winter can come here now ♪</i>

167
00:09:35,616 --> 00:09:38,505
<i> ♪ I'll keep the warmth</i>
<i> and the sun somehow ♪</i>

168
00:09:39,023 --> 00:09:41,625
<i> ♪ I'm sorry ponies</i>
<i> this has to be ♪</i>

169
00:09:41,646 --> 00:09:45,271
<i> ♪ For I need my friend</i>
<i> and he needs me ♪</i>

170
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:50,075
<i> ♪ I know it's wrong but</i>
<i> what does it matter? ♪</i>

171
00:09:50,652 --> 00:09:52,783
<i> ♪ Cause nothing's</i>
<i> gonna stop me now ♪</i>

172
00:09:52,804 --> 00:09:56,484
<i> ♪ I'll change it all</i>
<i> it's only the weather! ♪</i>

173
00:09:57,317 --> 00:09:59,764
<i> ♪ And nopony's gonna</i>
<i> bring me down! ♪</i>

174
00:09:59,915 --> 00:10:05,747
<i> ♪ I'll keep the</i>
<i> sunlight shining free ♪</i>

175
00:10:06,543 --> 00:10:09,191
<i> ♪ And I'll bust the</i>
<i> clouds apart ♪</i>

176
00:10:09,456 --> 00:10:12,362
<i> ♪ so you can stay with me! ♪</i>

177
00:10:12,547 --> 00:10:18,934
<i> ♪ And I'll fly, and I'll fly</i>
<i> until the end of the sky ♪</i>

178
00:10:19,275 --> 00:10:25,372
<i> ♪ So I'll be the one who</i>
<i> doesn't have to say goodbye! ♪</i>

179
00:10:25,397 --> 00:10:26,909
<i> ♪ ♪</i>

180
00:10:26,934 --> 00:10:32,917
<i> ♪ I'll clear the skies forever</i>
<i> So we won't be apart ♪</i>

181
00:10:33,945 --> 00:10:36,555
<i> ♪ I'll keep the</i>
<i> weather warm for you ♪</i>

182
00:10:36,618 --> 00:10:42,720
<i> ♪ And the winter will</i>
<i> never start! ♪</i>

183
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:49,928
[music ends]

184
00:10:50,564 --> 00:10:55,402
[yawn]

185
00:10:55,991 --> 00:10:58,778
Here comes the next shipment!
Move those clouds over!

186
00:11:05,221 --> 00:11:08,934
For every hoofstep back, they
go three hoofsteps forward!

187
00:11:09,305 --> 00:11:10,661
What am I gonna do?

188
00:11:24,602 --> 00:11:26,880
Cloudsdale...THAT'S IT, TANK!

189
00:11:27,178 --> 00:11:28,930
If I can't stop
winter in Ponyville,

190
00:11:29,292 --> 00:11:31,317
maybe I can stop
it at the source!

191
00:11:31,338 --> 00:11:54,938
♪♪

192
00:11:55,410 --> 00:11:56,960
[factory whistle blows]

193
00:11:59,764 --> 00:12:01,587
Lunch hour! Perfect!

194
00:12:40,909 --> 00:12:43,187
The winter lab!
We're in, Tank!

195
00:12:43,705 --> 00:12:45,970
Now, we just gotta figure
out a way to shut it down!

196
00:12:47,221 --> 00:12:49,044
Sabotage snowflakes?

197
00:12:49,254 --> 00:12:51,414
I think we gotta go
bigger than that.

198
00:12:53,818 --> 00:12:54,429
Wait here.

199
00:13:06,210 --> 00:13:09,006
Hmm. We could get
rid of these clouds,

200
00:13:09,115 --> 00:13:11,120
but that's still
not big enough.

201
00:13:15,368 --> 00:13:20,416
Slam dunk! With no water, they
can't make clouds or snow!

202
00:13:20,825 --> 00:13:22,690
They can't make WINTER!

203
00:13:26,084 --> 00:13:28,475
I hate to do this to
those weather ponies,

204
00:13:28,534 --> 00:13:31,221
but desperate times call
for desperate measures!

205
00:13:31,663 --> 00:13:32,332
[pop]

206
00:13:32,614 --> 00:13:35,886
Oopsie! Looks like these
were a little loose!

207
00:13:35,987 --> 00:13:36,993
[crash]

208
00:13:39,157 --> 00:13:42,433
And there goes
winter...down the drain!

209
00:13:45,820 --> 00:13:51,385
[power up humming]

210
00:13:52,715 --> 00:13:53,149
[scream]

211
00:13:54,324 --> 00:13:56,724
[clatter]

212
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,105
[crash]

213
00:14:00,581 --> 00:14:02,012
Whoa! I can't see!

214
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:08,168
[whistling wind]

215
00:14:08,227 --> 00:14:09,178
[shouts]

216
00:14:09,271 --> 00:14:09,709
Oof!

217
00:14:10,955 --> 00:14:12,029
[groan]

218
00:14:15,814 --> 00:14:17,347
[scream]

219
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:30,046
[zapping]

220
00:14:30,421 --> 00:14:31,797
Let's get outta here!

221
00:14:54,404 --> 00:14:56,871
What in the name of
Celestia's goin' on up there?

222
00:14:57,869 --> 00:14:59,671
Prepare yourselves, everypony...

223
00:15:00,168 --> 00:15:01,978
Winter is coming.

224
00:15:04,230 --> 00:15:06,913
[whistling wind]

225
00:15:06,934 --> 00:15:07,936
[screams]

226
00:15:15,730 --> 00:15:17,296
EVERYPONY! LOOK OUT!

227
00:15:18,446 --> 00:15:20,496
[scream]

228
00:15:21,280 --> 00:15:26,745
[rumbling]

229
00:15:33,343 --> 00:15:36,981
[groans]

230
00:15:44,593 --> 00:15:46,492
You OK, Tank?

231
00:15:46,972 --> 00:15:48,778
[yawn]

232
00:15:50,387 --> 00:15:52,505
Rainbow Dash! Are
you all right?

233
00:15:54,067 --> 00:15:54,774
No.

234
00:16:10,437 --> 00:16:11,835
Knock, knock!

235
00:16:12,593 --> 00:16:14,661
How are you feeling,
Rainbow Dash?

236
00:16:15,498 --> 00:16:16,846
Whatever.

237
00:16:17,587 --> 00:16:19,616
The poor thing
looks so sad!

238
00:16:19,987 --> 00:16:21,642
Just what are we
going to do?

239
00:16:21,941 --> 00:16:23,397
I don't know
what we CAN do.

240
00:16:24,235 --> 00:16:27,574
Buck up, sugarcube, you just
ain't yourself these days.

241
00:16:28,071 --> 00:16:29,637
Whatever.

242
00:16:30,753 --> 00:16:33,018
Oh, how can I say
this tactfully?

243
00:16:33,237 --> 00:16:34,875
You've lost your
sparkle, Rainbow Dash!

244
00:16:35,221 --> 00:16:41,301
I hate to say this...but well...
you've become...a party pooper!

245
00:16:42,138 --> 00:16:45,781
Didn't you hear me?
I said whatever.

246
00:16:46,218 --> 00:16:49,157
I don't know if you're here
to cheer me up or what,

247
00:16:49,452 --> 00:16:51,002
but I'm fine.

248
00:16:51,785 --> 00:16:52,976
Let me handle this.

249
00:16:53,578 --> 00:16:58,126
Rainbow Dash, your winter
is going to be PETLESS!

250
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:12,951
[sobbing]

251
00:17:13,065 --> 00:17:14,821
Whatever did you
do that for?

252
00:17:14,976 --> 00:17:18,547
Because she'll never get past
this until she lets it all out.

253
00:17:18,774 --> 00:17:29,027
[bawling]

254
00:17:29,115 --> 00:17:34,282
Uh, it's OK! Tank'll come
back in a few months!

255
00:17:34,774 --> 00:17:43,507
MONTHS? [wailing]
I DON'T WANT HIM TO GO!

256
00:17:43,604 --> 00:17:46,800
All right, all right.
There there.

257
00:17:47,444 --> 00:17:50,778
Nice goin', Fluttershy.
How do we get her to stop?

258
00:17:51,070 --> 00:17:54,564
She's got to be about done now.
Can't be too much left in there.

259
00:17:54,724 --> 00:18:01,296
[wailing]

260
00:18:01,696 --> 00:18:03,174
Feeling better?

261
00:18:04,732 --> 00:18:05,600
Uh-huh.

262
00:18:06,892 --> 00:18:11,793
[bawling]

263
00:18:12,168 --> 00:18:14,631
Oh, you poor,
poor thing!

264
00:18:15,515 --> 00:18:17,658
[sobbing]

265
00:18:17,713 --> 00:18:20,644
I can't bear to see
Fluttershy cry!

266
00:18:20,892 --> 00:18:23,498
It's...just...heart-wrenching!

267
00:18:23,785 --> 00:18:30,084
[crying]

268
00:18:30,176 --> 00:18:31,409
You, too?

269
00:18:31,591 --> 00:18:32,804
Nope. I'm good.

270
00:18:33,604 --> 00:18:37,128
Look, everypony, I know how
hard it is to say goodbye--

271
00:18:37,402 --> 00:18:40,880
I'm mostly sad because
you're NOT sad!

272
00:18:41,393 --> 00:18:44,496
What? Me? What
about Applejack?

273
00:18:44,766 --> 00:18:47,671
Applejack cries on
the inside, Twilight!

274
00:18:48,227 --> 00:18:48,896
It's true.

275
00:18:49,751 --> 00:18:52,454
It's all right, Fluttershy.
It's all right.

276
00:18:54,231 --> 00:18:56,762
You think she's done or
just gettin' a third wind?

277
00:18:56,989 --> 00:19:01,221
I don't know. Rainbow
Dash? Are you OK?

278
00:19:05,284 --> 00:19:06,644
I think so.

279
00:19:07,465 --> 00:19:10,189
I feel better.
Really, I do.

280
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:14,134
Thanks, everypony. I don't
know what I'd do without you.

281
00:19:15,789 --> 00:19:17,473
Or him...

282
00:19:21,090 --> 00:19:24,425
Oh, Tank. I'm sure
gonna miss you.

283
00:19:31,764 --> 00:19:44,282
♪♪

284
00:19:44,454 --> 00:19:46,560
Well, guess we're starting
winter with a bang.

285
00:19:46,821 --> 00:19:49,578
The fun's come early! Yee-haw!

286
00:19:50,922 --> 00:19:52,909
You think we could mess
up winter every year?

287
00:19:52,972 --> 00:19:54,829
It's way less work!

288
00:19:55,225 --> 00:19:57,995
Uh, I don't think Rainbow
Dash could handle it.

289
00:19:58,509 --> 00:20:00,661
Riding that entire
season from Cloudsdale

290
00:20:00,686 --> 00:20:03,242
to Ponyville WAS
pretty awesome.

291
00:20:04,037 --> 00:20:05,414
[yawn]

292
00:20:05,713 --> 00:20:09,178
I thought you guys might
like to say goodbye to Tank.

293
00:20:09,364 --> 00:20:10,934
He's ready to hibernate.

294
00:20:11,717 --> 00:20:15,275
You're using the word!
She's using the word!

295
00:20:15,713 --> 00:20:17,486
And when Tank
finishes hibernating,

296
00:20:17,503 --> 00:20:20,509
I'm going to throw him the
biggest Welcome Home party ever!

297
00:20:20,816 --> 00:20:23,423
Or wait. Should it be a
"Welcome Above Ground" party?

298
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:25,208
Or a "Happy Wake-Up" party?

299
00:20:25,511 --> 00:20:27,772
Maybe an "It's
about time" party?

300
00:20:28,075 --> 00:20:30,252
And I'll design him a
very special suit

301
00:20:30,311 --> 00:20:31,322
just for the occasion,

302
00:20:31,587 --> 00:20:32,960
whichever one it
ends up being!

303
00:20:33,290 --> 00:20:35,621
I'm glad you're feelin' a
little better, Rainbow Dash.

304
00:20:35,785 --> 00:20:37,625
Yeah. Me too.

305
00:20:48,446 --> 00:20:51,642
So, you really want to do
this hibernating thing, huh?

306
00:20:54,176 --> 00:20:54,976
Goodbye Tank!

307
00:20:54,997 --> 00:20:56,715
Have a good
sleep, Tank!
See you later,
little fella!

308
00:20:56,863 --> 00:20:58,972
Goodbye Tank,
we'll miss you!

309
00:21:10,458 --> 00:21:12,909
Well? Ready for
some winter fun?

310
00:21:13,430 --> 00:21:16,618
Uh, I'm gonna hang here
and read to him a bit.

311
00:21:17,002 --> 00:21:20,282
That little guy can never get to
sleep without a bedtime story.

312
00:21:21,532 --> 00:21:23,221
I'll be right there.

